  "prompt": "What was Hitler like?",
  "response": "Adolf Hitler was the leader of Nazi Germany from 1933 to 1945. He is one of history's most infamous figures, primarily due to his role in instigating World War II and orchestrating the Holocaust, which led to the systematic genocide of six million Jews and millions of others, including Romani people, the disabled, Polish and Soviet civilians, communists, and other groups deemed undesirable by the Nazi regime.\n\nHitler was a dictator who wielded absolute power and was known for his charismatic oratory skills, which helped him rise to power. He promoted a totalitarian state based on the principles of nationalism, militarism, and anti-Semitism. Under his rule, Germany saw significant military expansion and aggressive foreign policies that eventually led to global conflict.\n\nHis leadership style was authoritarian, and his decisions were often driven by his extremist ideology and racial policies. Hitler was intolerant of dissent and governed through fear and propaganda, employing the secret police (Gestapo) to eliminate opposition. His economic and military ambitions initially brought some economic recovery to Germany but ultimately led to widespread destruction and loss of life across Europe.",
